Xylem Inc. (XYL) , the water company spun
off by ITT Corp., acquired closely held MultiTrode Pty Ltd. of
Australia for about $26 million to expand monitoring and control
services.  MultiTrode helps water and wastewater companies cut
operating costs by reducing energy consumption, failures and
overflows,  White Plains , New York-based Xylem said in a
statement today.  MultiTrode, founded in 1986, has about 60 employees and
offices in Australia, the U.S. and U.K., Xylem said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tina Davis at 
 tinadavis@bloomberg.net  